Roadmap in order of planned implementation
   
 status command line option
    -gives date of last snapshot and lists recent package changes
    
 pickle
    -in create_snapshot and set_default
    -testing
    
 delete_snapshot 
    -should consolidate package change info, unless there is no parent
    
 list command
    -list only lists the last few ancestors with package changes
    -optionally indicate the number of ancestors to list
    
 tree view command
    -simple view with just names
    -view with change stats
    -detailed view with all consolidated changes
    
 tag snapshot
    append/replace tag after the date part of the name
    -add option to "create" command
    -deal with rollback default n=1 and tag
    
 factor in stuff from Chousuke
    -snapshot frequency throttling
    -snapshot disabling by shell var presence
    
 snapshot cleaning
    -command line clean [apt|tmp|crash] option
 
 delete_older_than 
    -to keep tree intact
    - should not delete tagged snapshots
    - nor snapshots with multiple children 
    -manual deletion is always possible
 
 rollback and setdefault should? prompt for a tag for the abandoned subvolume
 
 single instance
    -http://stackoverflow.com/questions/380870/python-single-instance-of-program
    -3rd answer
 
 update man page
